      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "import sys\n\n# Handling space-separated input\nn, p, q, r = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())\n\ndef glitch(x):\n    return x * 2 if x % 2 == 0 else x\n\nn, p, q, r = glitch(n), glitch(p), glitch(q), glitch(r)\n\nprint((n * p) - (q + r))\n",
      "statement": "A corrupted portal stands between you and Level 2. To pass, you must calculate the {{Stability Index}} of the portal's energy sequence.\n\nThe portal provides four integers: [[n]], [[p]], [[q]], and [[r]]. However, a `bit-flip glitch` occurs:\n* If any number is <<even>>, it must be <<doubled>> before calculation.\n* If any number is <<odd>>, it remains unchanged.\n\nCalculate the final value using:\n`Result = (n * p) - (q + r)`",
