    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A corrupted portal stands between you and Level 2. To pass, you must calculate the <const>Stability Index</const> of the portal's energy sequence.<br><br>The portal provides four integers: <var>n</var>, <var>p</var>, <var>q</var>, and <var>r</var>. However, a <pre style=\"font-family: monospace\">bit-flip glitch</pre> occurs:<br>* If any number is <strong>even</strong>, it must be <strong>doubled</strong> before calculation.<br>* If any number is <strong>odd</strong>, it remains unchanged.<br><br>Calculate the final value using:<br><pre style=\"font-family: monospace\">Result = (n * p) - (q + r)</pre></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> Four space-separated integers <var>n</var>, <var>p</var>, <var>q</var>, and <var>r</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer representing the calculated <const>Stability Index</const>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>n</var>, <var>p</var>, <var>q</var>, <var>r</var> &le; 1000</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">3 4 2 5</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-